<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/9805> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #9805" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/25> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "p. 257-63" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7173> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7173" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Tr. pl. 62, and Aed. ca. 59? (MRR 2.174, 189), and L. (Calpurnius) Bestia (25), Aed. by 57 (MRR 2.201). Although Münzer distinguishes between these two, they should almost certainly be identified. See R. G. Austin, ed. Cicero Pro Caelio3 (Oxford, 1960), 154-157. The gentilicium of no. 25 is not given, and the aedileship precedes his prosecution in 56. In favor of two persons is Cicero's failure to mention the Catilinarian connections of the aedilicius (Phil. 11.11; 12.20; 13.26); in favor of one are the dates, recorded political activity, and omission of the praenomen (except in Sallust and Appian). (TJC; RS, CP)" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5079> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5079" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cic. Phil. 13.26, an aedilicius. Defended by Cicero from a charge of ambitus (Cic. QF 2.3.6, Feb. 11, 56; Cael. 26, a candidate for the praetorship)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5002> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5002" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cic. Phil. 11.11; 13.26. Tribune of the Plebs in 62, and candidate for a praetorship in 56, be probably held his aedileship between 60 and 58." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4899> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4899" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "A Catilinarian sympathizer, who in their plan was to give the signal for action by attacking Cicero (Brut. in Cic. Ad Brut. 1.17.1; Sall. Cat. 17.3; 43.1; App. BC 2.3). Taking office with Nepos on December 10, 63, he joined him in his attack on Cicero (Cic. Sull. 31; Ad Brut. 1.17.1; Plut. Cic. 23.1; Schol. Bob. 82, and 127 Stangl). See above, on Metellus Nepos." .
